nodes.title: Face Detector
widgets_values:
If the Face Detector is identifying objects that are not faces as faces, increase the value of "bbox_threshold".

That is the confidence threshold for face recognition.

If it's not picking up enough faces, decrease that value.

nodes.title: Size of the Small Faces
widgets_values:
This "SEGS Filter range" node separates small face from large faces, detailing them in different ways.

Inside: anything within the min-max range.
Outside: anything beyond the min-max range.

If you see too many faces in the "Small Faces (SEGSPreview)" node, lower the "max_value".

Watch this YT tutorial for more information:
https://youtu.be/9ih35D2exMU

nodes.title: Hands Detailer
widgets_values:
This Hands Detailer function uses a diffusion model based on Stable Diffusion 1.5 because no fine-tuned SDXL model for hands anatomy has been released, yet. 

Once one will be available, select it in the Load Checkpoint node and change the OpenPose ControlNet model to the SDXL version, too.


For more information on this function:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DoyqCjKdojY

nodes.title: Refiner Steps
widgets_values:
If you don't want the SDXL Refiner model to perform any step (useful when you use a fine-tuned SDXL Base model), set the "refiner_start" to 1. 

––

Scheduler & Sampler Combination List

Fast with Good Convergence, Good Quality Image:

DPM++ 2M Exponential, 20-30 steps (can also use Karras
UniPC, 20-30 steps

High Quality, Poor Convergence:

DPM++ SDE Karras, 10-15 steps (can also use exponential scheduler)

DDIM, 10-15 steps

Ancestral, No Convergence, Fast, Good Quality

DPM++ SDE w/o Karras also good.          



Extra, extraneous information... 

- Best Quality = DPM++ SDE (+ Karras var.)

– DPM++ (dmpp) with Karras, DPM2 = More Accurate, Slower than DPM

- DPM-a stands for adaptive, exception to rule below. 

Ancestral Samplers = [Name] + "a", Adds noise each step, results in randomness

UniPC, HQ Image in 5-10 steps.

LMS with Karras

Outdated: DDIM & PLMS
Inferior & Old: Heun (is a 2nd order, slower)

Optimal resolution for SDXL 1024px model
with aspect ratio 16:9: 1344 x 768

nodes.title: Experimental Functions
widgets_values:
AP Workflow v5.0 includes the following experimental functions:


*Free Lunch (v1 and v2)

AI researchers have discovered an optimization for Stable Diffusion models that improves the quality of the generated images. For more information, read:
https://arxiv.org/abs/2309.11497

The Free Lunch technique requires the FreeU experimental node, which is not optimized for MPS and DirectML devices. On these systems, the node requires the CPU rather than the GPU, slowing down the image generation process.

Hence, it's bypassed by default. To enable it, un-bypass it with CTRL+B.

A refinement of the Free Lunch technique has been recently discovered, leading to the availability of a FreeU v2 node. 

The FreeU v1 and v2 nodes is located just above the XY Plot sub-function.


*Choose Image to proceed

A new experimental node, developed by u/Old_System7203, allows users to generate a batch of images with the Base/Fine-Tuned SDXL model and then pick the favorite image to continue the workflow with the Refiner, the Detailers (Hands and Faces), and the Upscalers. 

The node is bypassed by default. To enable it, un-bypass it with CTRL+B.

The node is located just above the "SDXL Refiner" section.


*Universal Negative Prompt

The user /u/AI_Characters has identified a "Universal Negative Prompt", which tends to improve the quality of most images with a single subject/concept.

For more information, read: 
https://civitai.com/articles/2141/good-universal-negative-prompt-for-sdxl-10 

In my tests, it works very well but it makes very difficult to generate images with multiple subjects/concepts. Hence, it's not enabled by default.

To enable it, you must:

1. Change input to 2 in the "Negative Prompt" switch in the "Universal Negative Prompt" section
2. Change input to 4 in the "Negative Prompt" switch in the "T2I" section of the workflow.

nodes.title: Auxiliary Functions
widgets_values:
AP Workflow v5.0 includes the following advanced functions:


*XY Plot
The "XY Plot" auxiliary function will generate images using with the SDXL Base+Refiner models, or just the Base/Fine-Tuned SDXL model, according to your configuration.

Activate it via the auxiliary switch in the Functions section of the workflow.

Notice that the XY Plot function can work in conjunction with ControlNet, the Detailers (Hands and Faces), and the Upscalers.


*ControlNet, Control-LoRAs, and LoRAs
You can condition your images with the ControlNet preprocessors, including the new OpenPose preprocessor compatible with SDXL, ControlLoRAs, and LoRAs.

Currently, up to six ControlNet preprocessors can be configured to work concurrently, but you can add additional ControlNet stack nodes if you wish.

Activate ControlNet and ControlLoRAs via the auxiliary switch in the Functions section of the workflow.

Then, activate each one ControlNet/ControlLoRA model you wish to use via its dedicated switch in the "ControlNet XL + Control-LoRAs" section of the workflow.

Activate each LoRA with its dedicated switch in the "Checkpoint Loader" section of the workflow.

Notice that ControlNet and ControlLoRAS can work in conjunction with the XY Plot function, the Refiner, the Detailers (Hands and Faces), and the Upscalers.


*Prompt Enricher
You can invoke the use of OpenAI GPT-4 or GPT-3.5-Turbo models to enrich your positive prompt. 

You'll need your OpenAPI API key for this feature to work, and you will be charged every time the node is active and you queue a new image generation.

WARNING: even if your prompt doesn't change, the node will make an API call, costing you money. So it's good practice to enable the Prompt Enricher feature only for one generation and then disable it immediately after.

Activate the Prompt Enricher via the auxiliary switch in the Functions section of the workflow.

nodes.title: Advanced Functions (2)
widgets_values:
AP Workflow v5.0 includes the following advanced functions:


*ReVision
As an alternative to the SDXL Base+Refiner models, or the Base/Fine-Tuned SDXL model, you can generate images with the ReVision method.

To use ReVision, you must enable it in the "Functions" section. You must also disable the Base+Refiner SDXL option and Base/Fine-Tuned SDXL option in the "Functions" section.

Notice that ReVision can work in conjunction with the Detailers (Hands and Faces) and the Upscalers.

Also notice that the ReVision model does NOT take into account the positive prompt defined in the Prompt Builder section, but it considers the negative prompt.


*Face Swapper
You can swap the face of one or more subjects in any image with the face of choice. 

If your source image has multiple faces, you can target the desired one via an index value. 

You can swap faces in individual images or all images in a directory. In either case, you must load the target image in the I2I section of the workflow.

Notice that Face Swapper can work in conjunction with the Upscaler.

Activate the Face Swapper via the auxiliary switch in the Functions section of the workflow.

nodes.title: Debug Functions
widgets_values:
AP Workflow v5.0 includes the following debug functions:


*Prompt and Parameters print
Both negative and positive prompt, together with a number of parameters, are printed in the terminal to provide more information about the ongoing image generation.

You can also write some personal notes about the next generation that will be printed in the terminal in the next run.

This information can be further saved in a file by adding the appropriate node, if you desire so.


*Universal Negative Prompt print
A string printed in the terminal will inform you if the Universal Negative Prompt is used or not.


*Images metadata compatible with A1111 WebUI / Vladmandic SD.Next / SD Prompt Reader
All images are saved with details about the prompts and the generation parameters that should be readable by other Stable Diffusion applications and image readers.

--

If you need to file an issue on GitHub with the author of a custom node suite, and you can't find the name of the suite a node belongs to, search for its name on this webpage: https://ltdrdata.github.io

--

NOTICE: All experimental/temporary nodes are in blue.

nodes.title: Advanced Functions (1)
widgets_values:
AP Workflow v5.0 includes the following advanced functions:


*Hand Detailer
The Hand Detailer will identify hands in the image and attempt to improve their anatomy through two consecutive passes, generating an image after processing.

The resulting image will be then passed to the Face Detailer (if enabled) and/or to the Upscalers (if enabled).

The Hand Detailer uses a dedicated ControlNet and Checkpoint based on SD 1.5. It works even if your base model is SDXL or Fine-Tuned SDXL.

To use the Hand Detailer you must enable it in the "Functions" section.


*Face Detailer
The Face Detailer will identify small and large faces, generating higher resolution for both, and attempting to improve their aesthetics according to two independent configurations (large faces require a different treatment than small faces).

The Face Detailer will generate an image after processing small faces and another after processing small and large faces. The resulting image will be then passed to the Upscalers (if enabled)

To use the Hand Detailer you must enable it in the "Functions" section.


*Upscalers
You can upscale your image, generated by the SDXL Base+Refiner models, the Base/Fine-Tuned SDXL model, or the ReVision model, with one or two upscalers in sequence.

If you have enabled the Detailers (Hands and/or Faces), the upscalers will only upscale those images.

To use just one or both upscalers, you must enable them in the "Functions" section.

nodes.title: Prompt Guidance
widgets_values:
From the documentation (https://github.com/comfyanonymous/ComfyUI):

You can use () to change the emphasis of a word or phrase like: (good code:1.2) or (bad code:0.8). The default emphasis for () is 1.1. To use () characters in your actual prompt escape them like \( or \).

You can use {day|night}, for wildcard/dynamic prompts. With this syntax "{wild|card|test}" will be randomly replaced by either "wild", "card" or "test" by the frontend every time you queue the prompt. To use {} characters in your actual prompt escape them like: \{ or \}.

Dynamic prompts also support C-style comments, like // comment or /* comment */.

To use a textual inversion concepts/embeddings in a text prompt put them in the models/embeddings directory and use them in the CLIPTextEncode node like this (you can omit the .pt extension):

embedding:embedding_filename.pt

nodes.title: Basic Functions
widgets_values:
AP Workflow v5.0 includes the following basic functions:


*Text2Image (T2I) with:

**SDXL Base+Refiner
All images are generated using both the SDXL Base model and the Refiner model, each automatically configured to perform a certain amount of diffusion steps according to the "Step Ratio" formula defined in the dedicated widget.

To use the Refiner, you must enable it in the "Functions" section and you must set the "refiner_start" parameter to a value between 0.1 and 0.99 in the "Parameters" section.


**Fine-tuned SDXL (or just the SDXL Base)
All images are generated just with the SDXL Base model or a fine-tuned SDXL model that requires no Refiner.

If you don't want to use the Refiner, you must disable it in the "Functions" section, and then set the "refiner_start" parameter to 1 in the "Parameters" section.


*Prompt Builder 
You can use a (very simple) prompt builder to quickly switch between your three most used types and styles of image for the positive prompt, and your three most used prompts for negative prompts. Or you can just have the old-fashioned single prompt box.


*Image2Image (I2I)
To use the Image2Image (I2I) function, simply disable the "Base/Fine-Tuned SDXL" and "Refiner" functions in the Functions section, and enable the functions you want to use on the uploaded image: Hand Detailer, Face Detailer, Upscaler, or Face Swap.

The I2I function supports individual images upload and as well as entire directories of images.

nodes.title: Prompt Enrichment (ChatGPT)
widgets_values:
You are a prompt generator for Dall-E. I'll pass you a text that describes an image. Identify the key elements of the description and enrich each of them by adding many details, also adding some final some words describing the high quality of the image.

For example, if I pass you the text "a yellow box sits on the table", you will have to enrich "a yellow box", "sits", and "on the table" by adding details to each one.

To enrich the text, follow these additional rules:

1. Do not comment on the task or write introductory text. For example, do not say things like "The image presents a yellow box sitting on a table..." or "In the image, a yellow box sits on a table...". Just describe the image with something like "a yellow box sits on a table..."

2. Do not output anything except the enriched paragraph describing the image.

3. Do not capitalize the first letter of the paragraph.

4. End the paragraph without a period.
